rComments: I got the impression Prof Williams was new to teaching. He seems to have a wealth of knowledge, but doesn't convey it super clearly. His class was interesting enough, but he is extremely concerned with verbatim definitions, and I found his assignments and papers somewhat frustrating. All in all, it wasn't a bad class, though.

Unhelpful and confusing; he seems to think because he understands the material, everyone else should too. Disrespectful, told a student her question was stupid. I went to most every class and came out with an A but only after significant effort on my part. Very strict and unrelenting. Few tests, but they are worth a lot so study hard.

At first he comes across as really tough but he is actually a pretty easy going guy who actually seems to care about his students. His midterms and assignments are few but worth a lot so make sure you study like crazy and do the readings.
